Governor Ben Ayade of Cross River State Friday began the distribution of face/nose mask to  residents of the state to prevent the spread of COVID 19 which has become a threat to survival of mankind. Answering questions from journalists at the Calabar Garment Factory shortly after the commencing the distribution of face/nose mask to residents of the state, the Governor said it has become pertinent for every resident of the state to be afraid of the virus which is spreading like a wild fire. The Governor whose announcement of released of two months’ salary advance which according to the Governor will provide succor to the factory workers. Ayade stated that food shall also be made available to vulnerable families whom according to his estimation lacked capacity to provide 2 square meals for their families. “I want you people to be afraid of the spread of the virus. It is only when you fear the virus, that is when you protect yourself from getting infected with the virus. “My duty is to protect my people from getting infected with the virus “. Section 14(2) of the constitution of the federal Republic of Nigeria is that the primary purpose of government is to protect my citizens”. “Its the reasons that I have to be at the Calabar Itu bridge to prevent people from entering the state”. The Governor maintained. The Governor stated that he was going to make sure that every one residing in the state have a nose mask to curb the spread of the virus especially now that Cross River neighboring states have confirmed cases of the disease. The Governor stated that it is pertinent for everyone residing in the state to protect he or herself from the spread of the virus giving the fact that Cross River shares a common boundary with the Cameroon, Ebonyi,Akwa Ibom and Benue States which had already reported outbreak of the disease.